n></b><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"> [ unconfirmed individual ] =E2=80=
=93 we will require the builder to cut inspection holes in the wall linings=
 so testing can be completed within the wall cavities.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">The intention is to=
 test for smoke and chemical contamination within the wall cavities, and on=
 the exposed surfaces downstairs. There will be a significant number of sam=
ple sites [tests] to be completed to
 be able to author a reliable report. After initial testing is completed, o=
ur intention is to apply restorative cleaning methods to targeted individua=
l sample sites, followed by subsequent testing, post-cleaning, to provide d=
ata to measure the effectiveness
 of cleaning/decontamination.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">All samples taken f=
rom site will require laboratory analysis before being incorporated into a =
report. This process may take up to 10 working days =E2=80=93 so we want to=
 capture swab samples from surfaces before and
 after the decontamination process is undertaken.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
